    "last_activity_date" : 1702811698,
    "last_edit_date" : 1702811698,
    "creation_date" : 1390205351,
    "answer_id" : 21228966,
    "question_id" : 2889238,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p><strong>Changing keystore password</strong></p>\n<pre class=\"lang-none prettyprint-override\"><code>$ keytool -storepasswd -keystore keystorename\nEnter keystore password:  &lt;old password&gt;\nNew keystore password: &lt;new password&gt;\nRe-enter new keystore password: &lt;new password&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<p><strong>Changing keystore alias password</strong></p>\n<pre class=\"lang-none prettyprint-override\"><code>$ keytool -keypasswd -keystore keystorename -alias aliasname\nEnter keystore password:  \nNew key password for &lt;aliasname&gt;: \nRe-enter new key password for &lt;aliasname&gt;:\n</code></pre>\n<p>Note:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>keystorenam</code>: name of your keystore (with path if you are in different folder)</li>\n<li><code>aliasname</code>: alias name you used when creating (if name has space you can use <code>\\)</code></li>\n</ul>\n<p>For example:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-none prettyprint-override\"><code>$ keytool -keypasswd -keystore keystorename -alias stop\\ watch\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2704546,
      "reputation" : 2407,
      "user_id" : 2334422,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/Kd6CO.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Ishan Liyanage",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2334422/ishan-liyanage"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 8,
    "last_activity_date" : 1392022159,
    "creation_date" : 1392022159,
    "answer_id" : 21672520,
    "question_id" : 2889238,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If the keystore contains other key-entries with different password you have to change them also or you can isolate your key to different keystore using below command,</p>\n\n<pre><code>keytool -importkeystore  -srckeystore mystore.jck -destkeystore myotherstore.jks -srcstoretype jceks\n-deststoretype jks -srcstorepass mystorepass -deststorepass myotherstorepass -srcalias myserverkey\n-destalias myotherserverkey -srckeypass mykeypass -destkeypass myotherkeypass\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 232032,
      "reputation" : 5256,
      "user_id" : 496601,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 96,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/de035756303c544e06d1d7bab6179fe1?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "whyoz",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/496601/whyoz"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 6,
    "last_activity_date" : 1464815550,
    "creation_date" : 1464815550,
    "answer_id" : 37578866,
    "question_id" : 2889238,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>There are so many answers here, but if you're trying to change the jks password on a Mac in Android Studio.  Here are the easiest steps I could find</p>\n\n<p>1) Open Terminal and cd to where your .jks is located</p>\n\n<p>2) <strong>keytool -storepasswd -new NEWPASSWORD -keystore YOURKEYSTORE.jks</strong></p>\n\n<p>3) enter your current password</p>\n"
  }, {
